<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="528" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="528" targetBox="[164,755,1830,2244]" targetPageId="131">
<paragraph blockId="131.[778,1370,1828,2252]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[778,954,2183,2212]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">Distribution.</emphasis>
West Africa in Sierra Leone, SE Guinea, Ivory Coast, and SW Ghana;it
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="131.[161,1369,2256,2879]" box="[165,488,2256,2289]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">might occur in Liberia.</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="528" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="131.[161,1369,2256,2879]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,412,2296,2329]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 78-101 mm,tail 34-55 mm, hindfoot 13-16 mm; weight 7-18-4 g. Therese’s White-toothed Shrew is medium-sized to relatively large. Dorsal pelage is gray to brown, and ventral pelage is whitish, with no clear demarcation between the two. Feet are brown. Tail is 39-62% of head-body length, thick, and covered with sparse brown hairs. There are three unicuspids. Chromosomal complement has 2n = 50 and FN = 82-84.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[163,1217,2532,2565]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="131.[161,1369,2256,2879]" box="[163,1217,2532,2565]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[163,275,2532,2565]" pageId="131" pageNumber="528">Habitat.</emphasis>
Various grassland habitats and rice fields at elevations of ¢.1600 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
